The paper deals with a visualization technique for multi-dimensional data, which is a common topic in Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) and Graphics (cs.GR). The technique involves rendering polylines based on their slope, which could also be relevant to Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Computational Geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the paper mentions linear time computation, which suggests a possible connection to Data Structures (cs.DS).
